<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Different" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Different,</orth> 1) unlike, dissimilar: <cit><quote>much d. from the man he was,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 46</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>d. in blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.135" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 135</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.5.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 5, 92</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.3.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 3, 37</bibl>.<lb />2) various, other, not the same: <cit><quote>the sweet smell of d. flowers in odour and in hue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 98.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 98, 6</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lc 125" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.264" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 264</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.257" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 257</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.1.179" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 1, 179</bibl>.

